headline: Smurfit Westrock (NYSE:SW) One-Off $456M Loss Challenges Bullish Margin and Growth Narratives
summary: Smurfit Westrock (SW) just reported profit margins of 2.4%, nearly doubling last year’s 1.3%, and delivered blockbuster EPS growth of 238.5% over the past twelve months. That surge comes despite a significant one-off loss of $456.0 million in the most recent period, which weighed on results up to September 30, 2025. With earnings projected to climb 29.5% per year and the share price sitting at $36.04, far below fair value and analyst targets, the setup hints at optimism for investors willing...
